A more detailed analysis of the biophysical properties of TIM-1–ligand interactions was conducted by fitting the acquired DFS data to the Bell-Evans model. The model describes the influence of an external force on the rate of bond dissociation45. According to this model, a pulling force, f, distorts the intermolecular potential of a ligand-receptor complex, leading to a lowering of the activation energy and an increase in the dissociation rate k(f) as follows:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
